The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Artistic appeal

 Focusing on topical, social and human issues, the ongoing exhibition of paintings and installations, presented by Indian Society of Contemporary Artists Group, features works by Jagannath Chatterjee, Atanu Ghosh, Kanchan (one of his paintings appears above) and Kanchan Das. Conjuring up lucid, imaginative, suggestive and even futuristic visions of life and the future of our universe, the collection on display emphasizes the need for global peace and harmony and the dangers of man?s detachment from nature and his roots.

 Event: An exhibition of paintings and installations

 When: Till October 20, 3 pm - 8 pm

 Where: Academy of Fine Arts, South Gallery




